TranslatedText._content:
AEENDY = AEENDTC -RFSTDTC+1 if AEENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. AEENDTC - RFSTDTC if AEENDTC
precedes RFSTDTC

AESTDY = AESTDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if AESTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. AESTDTC - RFSTDTC if
AESTDTC precedes RFSTDTC

MethodDef.Name: Algorithm to derive the AETRTEM flag

TranslatedText._content:
AETRTEM = "Y" if Adverse Event was not present prior to the RFSTDTC, or it was present
prior to the RFSTDTC but increased in severity during the treatment period. Null otherwise.

Age at Screening Date (Screening Date - Birth date). For the complete algorithm see the
referenced external document.

Only created if value qualifies as potentially clinically significant high or low based on
the high and low ranges specified in the Statistical Analysis Plan.

CMENDY = CMENDTC - RFSTDTC +1 if CMENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. CMENDTC - RFSTDTC if
CMENDTC precedes RFSTDTC

CMSTDY = CMSTDTC - RFSTDTC +1 if CMSTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. CMSTDTC - RFSTDTC if
CMSTDTC precedes RFSTDTC

DADY = DADTC - RFSTDTC+1 if DADTC is on or after RFSTDTC. DADTC - RFSTDTC if DADTC precedes
RFSTDTC.
DASTRESN = numeric value of DAORRES, when DAORRES contains numeric data.

DSSTDY = DSSTDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if DSSTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. DSSTDTC - RFSTDTC if
DSSTDTC precedes RFSTDTC. Null if RFSTDTC is Null.

Safety subjects only: EGBLFL = "Y" for last record with non Null EGORRES on or before the
first dose date (RFSTDTC). Null otherwise
EGDRVFL = "Y" for derived EGTESTCDs QTCB and QTCF. Null otherwise.

EGDY = EGDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if EGDTC is on or after RFTSDTC. EGDTC - RFSTDTC if EGDTC precedes
RFSTDTC.

Data collected in non-standard units is converted using standard conversion factors to
standard units.
EGSTRESN = numeric value of EGSTRESC, when EGSTRESC contains numeric data.

If ARMCD=WONDER10 then EXDOSE = Number of Tablets per Day (QVAL where QNAM=SMNO) * 10. If
ARMCD=WONDER20 then EXDOSE = Number of Tablets per Day (QVAL where QNAM=SMNO) * 20. If ARMCD=PLACEBO then EXDOSE = 0.
Derived from ARM, ARMCD - equal to mg

EXENDY = EXENDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if EXENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. EXENDTC - RFSTDTC if EXENDTC
precedes RFSTDTC.

EXSTDY = EXSTDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if EXSTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. EXSTDTC - RFSTDTC if
EXSTDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

Safety subjects only: LBBLFL = "Y" for last record with non Null LBORRES on or before the
first dose date (RFSTDTC). Null otherwise.

LBDY = LBDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if LBDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. LBDTC - RFSTDTC if LBDTC precedes
RFSTDTC.
Reference Range Indicator based upon standard results and ranges.

PEDY = PEDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if PEDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. PEDTC - RFSTDTC if PEDTC precedes
RFSTDTC.

Safety subjects only: QSBLFL = "Y" for last record with non Null QSORRES on or before the
first dose date (RFSTDTC). Null otherwise.

QSDY= QSDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if QSDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. QSDTC - RFSTDTC if QSDTC precedes
RFSTDTC.

If questionnaire result is a numerically relevant code then code stored here; else
character result equal to QSORRES. Character results contain mixed case data.
When QSORRES is numeric then QSSTRESN equal to numeric result

QTcB = QT interval / square root of (60 / heart rate). For the complete algorithm see the
referenced external document.

QTcF = QT interval / cubic root of (60 / heart rate). For the complete algorithm see the
referenced external document.
Domain abbreviation from where data originated.
All records for the same USUBJID with the same RELID are considered related.
RFENDTC = termination date, for safety subjects. Null for screen failures.
RFSTDTC = first date/time of study drug, for safety subject. Null for screen failures.

MethodDef.Name: Algorithm to derive the SAFETY population flag

TranslatedText._content:
SAFETY = "Y" for randomized subjects who took at least one dose study medication. Null
otherwise.

SCDY = SCDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if SCDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. SCDTC - RFSTDTC if SCDTC precedes
RFSTDTC.

If Element = SCREEN, derived from SVENDTC where VISIT = SCREENING. If Element = EOS,
derived from DS where DSCAT = DISPOSITION EVENT or from the latest EXENDTC from EX whichever is later. For treatment Elements,
derived from last EXENDTC for the element. For the complete algorithm see the referenced external document.
Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID in the domain.

If Element = SCREEN, derived from SVSTDTC where VISIT = SCREENING or from DS where DSDECOD
= 'INFORMED CONSENT', whichever is earliest. If Element = EOS, derived from DS where DSCAT = DISPOSITION EVENT. For treatment
Elements, derived from first EXSTDTC for the element. For the complete algorithm see the referenced external document.

SVSTDY = SVSTDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if SVSTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. SVSTDTC - RFSTDTC if SVSTDTC
precedes RFSTDTC.
Sequential number identifying records within each TSPARM in the domain.

FormalExpression.Context: SAS 9.0 or later, as part of a data step assignment or proc sql select and update statements.
